  "title": "feat(monorepo): introduce react-based InstantSearch flavours to the codebase",
  "body": "what i did:\r\n- change configs (jest, babel, eslint, typescript) to be the same between packages\r\n  - do some related linting/typing/test changes in InstantSearch.js\r\n- choose best between custom babel plugins and test utils\r\n- update extension-resolver babel plugin to work for local \"absolute\" packages\r\n- enable e2e tests for react and react-hooks (new)\r\n- rewrite commits with correct issue/pr links\r\n- add script to ensure versions stay synced in React InstantSearch \r\n\r\nwhat i didn't do:\r\n- consolidate between tests/mock and tests/mocks (there's an overlap, but required too much changes in tests for now - dependencies, types, etc.)\r\n- import from `@instantsearch/testutils` (similarly complicated babel, tests ...  changes. Can also be done later)\r\n- fix build output of react-instantsearch pacakge (already the case before migration)\r\n",
